C
P(A)=0; P(A^c\cap B^c\cap C^c)=0.4; P(C|A\cup B\cup C)=0.6; P(B^c\cap A^c|C)=5/6
P(A^c)=1; P(A^\cup B\cup C)=1-P(A^c\cap B^c\cap C^c)=0.6
P(C)=P(C|A\cup B\cup C)*P(A\cup B\cup C)=0.36
P(B^c\cap C)=P(B^c|C)P(C)=P(B^c\cap A^c|C)P(C)=5/6*0.36=0.3
P(B^c)=P(B^c\cap C)+P(B^c\cap C^c)=0.3+0.4=0.7
P(A^c\cap B\cap C^c)=P(B\cap C^c)=1-P(B^c\cup C)=1-(P(B^c)+P(C)-P(B^c\cap C))=1-(0.7+0.36-0.3)=0.24
P(C|(A^c\cap B^c)\cup (A^c\cap C^c))=P(C|B^c\cup C^c)=P(C\cap (B^c\cup C^c))/P(B^c\cup C^c)=
P(C\cap B^c)/P(B^c\cup C^c)=0.3/(0.7+(1-0.36)-0.4)
P(B^c\cup C^c)
P(B \cap C^c)=0.24, P(B^c \cap C)=0.3.
\frac{P(B^c \cap C)}{P(B^c \cap C)+P(B \cap C^c)}=\frac{0.3}{0.3+0.24}=\frac{5}{9}
